																		There Is No First SCP Curse!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2000367&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251600" alt="WrongJohnSilver" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2000367)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;" >WrongJohnSilver</a></span> <span class="odate time_1442866453 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">21 Sep 2015 20:14</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2379468">
									

<p>So there's been quite a bit of discussion about first SCPs, and how there is no &quot;First SCP Curse.&quot;</p>
<p>There isn't. If you take the time to make sure you know what you're doing, your first SCP can be wildly successful.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Here's&nbsp;a&nbsp;few&nbsp;famous&nbsp;first&nbsp;SCPs:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Here's&nbsp;a&nbsp;few&nbsp;famous&nbsp;first&nbsp;SCPs:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-1000">SCP-1000</a></li>
<li><a href="/scp-1193">SCP-1193</a></li>
<li><a href="/scp-1981">SCP-1981</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Take a look at those. 1000 has a lot of narrative and development, and 1981 has beautifully altered photos. But heck, 1193 isn't too long, has a simple story, and still packs a wallop.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Can a new author do what these did? Of course they can! It just means taking the time to understand what makes your writing great. And hey, you don't have to write a top-ranked SCP for it to work for your first one.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Here's&nbsp;a&nbsp;few&nbsp;more&nbsp;recent&nbsp;first&nbsp;SCPs&nbsp;that&nbsp;have&nbsp;survived&nbsp;and&nbsp;do&nbsp;well&nbsp;today:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Here's&nbsp;a&nbsp;few&nbsp;more&nbsp;recent&nbsp;first&nbsp;SCPs&nbsp;that&nbsp;have&nbsp;survived&nbsp;and&nbsp;do&nbsp;well&nbsp;today:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2124">SCP-2124</a></li>
<li><a href="/scp-2289">SCP-2289</a></li>
<li><a href="/scp-2323">SCP-2323</a></li>
<li><a href="/scp-2816">SCP-2816</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>And sometimes, the idea is just good enough, but starts out by sliding slowly into the negatives, but then the author, with a little advice, figures out what works and what doesn't, edits the article properly, and it survives in the end.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Here&nbsp;are&nbsp;a&nbsp;few&nbsp;examples&nbsp;of&nbsp;articles&nbsp;that&nbsp;successfully&nbsp;fended&nbsp;off&nbsp;the&nbsp;downvotes:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Here&nbsp;are&nbsp;a&nbsp;few&nbsp;examples&nbsp;of&nbsp;articles&nbsp;that&nbsp;successfully&nbsp;fended&nbsp;off&nbsp;the&nbsp;downvotes:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-2130">SCP-2130</a></li>
<li><a href="/scp-2192">SCP-2192</a></li>
<li><a href="/scp-2993">SCP-2993</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Note: all these Series III articles have appeared in the past&#8230; 8 months? This should be plenty of proof that yes, it is possible to have your idea survive, and no, you don't have to be a master author to have your first SCP article be a good one.</p>
<p>So, did you have a successful first SCP? Let's talk about the process you took to get it up! Are you a new author who really wants to get your idea on the wiki? Let's talk about what challenges you're facing!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;The&nbsp;Super&nbsp;Secret&nbsp;And&nbsp;Powerful&nbsp;Way&nbsp;To&nbsp;Get&nbsp;Your&nbsp;First&nbsp;SCP&nbsp;To&nbsp;Work&nbsp;With&nbsp;One&nbsp;Weird&nbsp;Trick!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;The&nbsp;Super&nbsp;Secret&nbsp;And&nbsp;Powerful&nbsp;Way&nbsp;To&nbsp;Get&nbsp;Your&nbsp;First&nbsp;SCP&nbsp;To&nbsp;Work&nbsp;With&nbsp;One&nbsp;Weird&nbsp;Trick!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>First and foremost, new authors, read and understand and follow the <a href="/guide-for-newbies">Guide for Newbies</a> and <a href="/how-to-write-an-scp">How To Write An SCP</a>. Seriously. Do that. All of the authors that made their first article stick did that. Past that, the stories are varied.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

